					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10792151#post-4196612</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10792151/scp-4905#post-4196612</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 25 Mar 2019 16:58:24 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ManyMeats</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2104082</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'd point out that I didn't call Vikings a &quot;race&quot;, I said,</p> <blockquote> <p>members of the human race culturally identifying as Vikings</p> </blockquote> <p>I don't begrudge your point about identifying as vikings/pirates but they did refer to themselves as Vikingr on the 3rd monolith. Whatever the practical or literal use of the word is on Earth, in this story that's what they labeled themselves while on the moon.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10792151#post-4196594</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10792151/scp-4905#post-4196594</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 25 Mar 2019 16:38:23 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ch00bakka</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1238719</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Nobody &quot;culturally identified&quot; as a Viking for the same reason that nobody &quot;culturally identified&quot; as a pirate. &quot;Viking&quot; is an occupation, not a culture. Also, calling the &quot;vikings&quot; a &quot;race&quot; is sketchy at best and sounds a lot like white-supremacist &quot;nordic race&quot; propaganda at worst.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
